{"word":"G5485 - χάρις - cháris - khar'-ece - Acceptable","slug":"G5485","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">χάρις</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>cháris"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khar'-ece"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Acceptable"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C7;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03B9;&#x03C2; - charis</b> - <i>khar'-ece</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G5463\">G5463</a>; <i>graciousness</i> (as <i>gratifying</i>), of manner or act (abstract or concrete; literal, figurative or spiritual; especially the divine influence upon the heart, and its reflection in the life; including <i>gratitude</i>): - acceptable, benefit, favour, gift, grace (-ious), joy liberality, pleasure, thank (-s, -worthy)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2168\">G2168</a>, <a href=\"#/G2169\">G2169</a>, <a href=\"#/G2170\">G2170</a>, <a href=\"#/G4796\">G4796</a>, <a href=\"#/G5463\">G5463</a>, <a href=\"#/G5479\">G5479</a>, <a href=\"#/G5483\">G5483</a>, <a href=\"#/G5484\">G5484</a>, <a href=\"#/G5486\">G5486</a>, <a href=\"#/G5487\">G5487</a>, <a href=\"#/G884\">G884</a>"}]}